### Paymanager — Payment Flow
### Requires: Silvergate running on :3002, Paymanager on :3000, Ingest on :3001

@base = http://localhost:3000

### Health check
GET {{base}}/health/ready

### -----------------------------------------------
### Instant capture (default)
### -----------------------------------------------

### 1. Create payment — instant capture (no delay)
POST {{base}}/api/v1/payments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "amount": 5000,
  "currency": "USD",
  "card_token": "tok_visa_4242"
}

> {%
    client.global.set("payment_id", response.body.id);
    client.log("Payment ID: " + response.body.id);
    client.log("Status: " + response.body.status);
%}

### 2. Get payment (run after ~1s to see captured)
GET {{base}}/api/v1/payments/{{payment_id}}

> {%
    client.log("Status: " + response.body.status);
%}

### -----------------------------------------------
### Delayed capture + void flow
### -----------------------------------------------

### 3. Create payment with 5 minute capture delay
POST {{base}}/api/v1/payments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "amount": 15000,
  "currency": "EUR",
  "card_token": "tok_mc_1234",
  "capture_delay": "5m"
}

> {%
    client.global.set("delayed_payment_id", response.body.id);
    client.log("Payment ID: " + response.body.id);
    client.log("Status: " + response.body.status);
    client.log("Capture At: " + response.body.capture_at);
%}

### 4. Check status — should be "authorized" (not captured yet)
GET {{base}}/api/v1/payments/{{delayed_payment_id}}

> {%
    client.log("Status: " + response.body.status);
%}

### 5. Void the payment (cancel before capture)
POST {{base}}/api/v1/payments/{{delayed_payment_id}}/void

> {%
    client.log("Void result: " + response.body.status);
%}

### 6. Verify voided status
GET {{base}}/api/v1/payments/{{delayed_payment_id}}

> {%
    client.log("Final status: " + response.body.status);
%}

### -----------------------------------------------
### Edge cases
### -----------------------------------------------

### 7. Void already captured payment (expect 409)
POST {{base}}/api/v1/payments/{{payment_id}}/void

> {%
    client.log("Expected conflict: " + response.status);
%}

### 8. Invalid request (expect 400)
POST {{base}}/api/v1/payments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "amount": -100,
  "currency": "XXXX",
  "card_token": ""
}

### 9. Non-existent payment (expect 404)
GET {{base}}/api/v1/payments/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
